  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective observational registry of CPB-circuit hemolysis measurements collected across 14 clinical sites, which the assessment narrative treats as functionally equivalent to a controlled bench experiment. The registry data span the same five flow-speed operating points targeted by the CFD model, and the resulting hemolysis indices align closely with simulation predictions (mean absolute error < 4%). The assessment team notes that the observational dataset provides rich real-world coverage that would be impractical to replicate in a controlled laboratory setting, and concludes that the evidence base is sufficient to support the Accepted decision.",
