      "name": "CFD hemolysis prediction vs. clinical registry — five operating points",
      "description": "Simulation-predicted relative hemolysis index (RHI) values at five flow-speed combinations were compared against RHI values derived from the 14-site observational registry. Agreement was assessed using mean absolute error (MAE = 3.7%) and Bland-Altman analysis (limits of agreement ±0.06 RHI units). All five operating points satisfied the RH < 1 acceptance criterion in both simulation and registry data, supporting the claim that the CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis conditions.",
